<h2>Symfony CLI</h2>

<p><a href="https://github.com/symfony-cli/symfony-cli">Symfony CLI</a> is a must-have tool when developing
Symfony applications on your local machine. It includes the
<a href="https://symfony.com/doc/current/setup/symfony_cli.html#running-the-local-web-server">Symfony Local Server</a>,
the best way to run local Symfony applications. This week Symfony CLI released
its new <a href="https://github.com/symfony-cli/symfony-cli/releases/tag/v5.13.0">5.13.0</a> version with the following changes:</p>

<ul>
<li>add Access-Control-Expose-Headers to CORS headers (@fnash)</li>
<li>Update remote.go to write DEFAULT_URI (@alexander-schranz)</li>
<li>Simplify settign DEFAULT_URI (@alexander-schranz)</li>
<li>Fix Docker client version (@fabpot)</li>
</ul>

